    "excerpt": "A text of the Qaddish using feminine language for God and for the rabbis and their students. Inspired by Rabbi Debi Shoua Haim of the Reform congregation Kol HaNeshama in Jerusalem, who, in a conversation about feminine-language versions of liturgical texts, challenged me to write a feminine Qaddish variant. . . .",
    "content": "<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\nA text of the Qaddish using feminine language for God and for the rabbis and their students. Inspired by Rabbi Debi Shoua Haim of the Reform congregation Kol HaNeshama in Jerusalem, who, in a conversation about feminine-language versions of liturgical texts, challenged me to write a feminine Qaddish variant.\n</div>\n<hr />\n<table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" class=\"draggable toggleable-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th id=\"x\" style=\"text-align: right;\">Source (Aramaic)</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Translation (English)</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"jpa-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nתִּתְגַדַּל וְתִתְקַדַּשׁ שְׁכִינְתָּא רַבְּתָא (<span class=\"instruction\">קהל –</span> אָמֵן)<br />\nבְּבִרְיָתָא דִּילִידַת כִּרְעוּתָהּ<br />\nוְתַשְׁלִיט שִׁלְטוֹנָהּ<br />\n<span style=\"color: red;\"><span class=\"instruction\">ספרדים</span> וְתַצְמַח פֻּרְקָנָהּ<br />\nוְתַבַּע לְעָלְמָא דְּאָתֵי (<span class=\"instruction\">קהל –</span> אָמֵן)</span><br />\nבְּחַיֵּיכוֹן וּבְיוֹמֵיכוֹן<br />\nוּבְחַיֵּי דְּכׇל־בֵּית יִשְׂרָאֵל<br />\nבַּעֲגַלָא וּבִזְמַן קָרִיב<br />\nוְאִמְרוּ אָמֵן׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nMagnified and sanctified be the great <span class=\"divine-referent\">Presence</span> (<span class=\"instruction\">community:</span> <em>Amen!</em>)<br />\nin the creation that <span class=\"divine-referent\">She</span> bore per <span class=\"divine-referent\">Her</span> will.<br />\nMay <span class=\"divine-referent\">Her</span> rulership rule<br />\n<span style=\"color: red;\"><span class=\"instruction\">Sephardim:</span> and <span class=\"divine-referent\">Her</span> salvation sprout<br />\nand <span class=\"divine-referent\">She</span> hasten the world to come (<span class=\"instruction\">community:</span> <em>Amen!</em>)</span></span><br />\nin your lives and in your days<br />\nin the lives of all Israel,<br />\nspeedily and in a soon time,<br />\nand say <em>amen</em>.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"jpa-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n(<span class=\"instruction\">קהל –</span> אָמֵן׃ תֶּהֱוֵי שְׁכִינְתָּא רַבְּתָא מְבָרָכָא<br />\nלְעָלַם וּלְעָלְמֵי עָלְמַיָּא׃)\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n(<span class=\"instruction\">community:</span> <em>Amen!</em> May <span class=\"divine-referent\">the Great Presence</span> be blessed<br />\nforever and ever and ever!)\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"jpa-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nתִּתְבָּרַךְ וְתִשְׁתַּבַּח<br />\nוְתִתְפָּאַר וְתִתְרוֹמַם<br />\nוְתִתְנַשֵּׂא וְתִתְהַדָּר וְתִתְעַלֶּה<br />\nוְתִתְהַלָּל שְׁכִינְתָּא קַדִּישְׁתָּא בְּרִיכָא הִיא (<span class=\"instruction\">קהל –</span> בְּרִיכָא הִיא)<br />\nלְעֵֽלָּא מִן־כׇּל־בִּרְכָן<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_1');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_1');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[1]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_1\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> בעשרת ימי תשובה לְעֵֽלָּא לְעֵֽלָּא מִכׇּל־בִּרְכָן&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_1', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> וְזִמְרִין תֻּשְׁבְּחָתָא וְנֶחָמָתָא<br />\nדַּאֲמִירָן בְּעָלְמָא<br />\nוְאִמְרוּ אָמֵן׃ (<span class=\"instruction\">קהל –</span> אָמֵן׃)<br />\n<span class=\"instruction\">סוף חצי קדיש</span>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nBlessed and lauded<br />\nand glorified and exalted<br />\nand elevated and extolled and revered<br />\nand praised be <span class=\"divine-referent\">the blessed holy Presence</span> (<span class=\"instruction\">community:</span> Blessed be <span class=\"divine-referent\">She</span>!)<br />\nhigh above<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_2');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_2');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[2]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_2\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> During the ten days of repentance: “high, high above”&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_2', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> all blessings and songs, lauds and consolations,<br />\nthat we say in this world,<br />\nand say <em>amen</em>.(<span class=\"instruction\">community:</span> <em>Amen!</em>)<br />\n<span class=\"instruction\">End of the Ḥatsi Qaddish.</span>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"jpa-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"instruction\">לקדיש דְּרַבָּתָנָן</span><br />\nעַל־יִשְׂרָאֵל<br />\nוְעַל־רַבָּתָנָן<br />\nוְעַל־תַּלְמִידְתֵּיהֵין<br />\nוְעַל־תַּלְמִידְתֵּי תַּלְמִידְתֵּיהֵין<br />\nוְעַל־כׇּל־מָאן דְּעוֹסְקָן בְּאוֹרַיְתָא<br />\nדִּי בְאַתְרָא<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_3');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_3');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_3\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[3]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_3\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> בארץ ישראל יש מוסיפין: קַדִּישָׁא&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_3').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_3', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> הָדֵין וְדִי בְכׇל־אֲתַר וַאֲתַר<br />\nיְהֵא לְהֵין וּלְכוֹן שְׁלָמָא רַבָּא<br />\nחִנָּא וְחִסְדָּא וְרַחֲמִין<br />\nוְחַיִּין אֲרִיכִין וּמְזוֹנֵי רְוִיחֵי<br />\nוּפֻרְקָנָא מִן־קֳדָם־אִמְהֵין דְּבִשְׁמַיָּא<br />\nוְאִמְרוּ אָמֵן׃ (<span class=\"instruction\">קהל –</span> אָמֵן׃)\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"instruction\">For the Qaddish d-Rabbatanan:</span><br />\nOn Israel<br />\nand on our <em>rabbatas</em><span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_4');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_4');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_4\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[4]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_4\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> A neologism, an Aramaic feminine form for “rabbis”&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_4').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_4', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nand on their students<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_5');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_5');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_5\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[5]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_5\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> An Aramaic feminine form, as opposed to the masculine form used in the traditional text&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_5').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_5', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nand on their students’ students<br />\nand on all those who delve in Torah,<br />\nwhether in this<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_6');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_6');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_6\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[6]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_6\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> In Israel, some add “holy”&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_6').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_6', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> place or in any place,<br />\nlet they and you have great peace,<br />\ngrace and kindness and compassion<br />\nand long life and ample sustenance<br />\nand salvation from before <span class=\"divine-referent\">their Mother in heaven</span>,<br />\nand say <em>amen</em>. (<span class=\"instruction\">community:</span> <em>Amen!</em>)\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"jpa-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"instruction\">לקדיש שלם</span><br />\nתִּתְקַבַּל צְלוֹתְהֵין וּבָעוּתְהֵין<br />\nדְּכׇל־בְּנַת־יִשְׂרָאֵל<br />\nקֳדָם־אִמְהֵין דְּבִשְׁמַיָּא<br />\nוְאִמְרוּ אָמֵן׃ (<span class=\"instruction\">קהל –</span> אָמֵן׃)\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"instruction\">For the Qaddish Shalem:</span><br />\nMay the prayers and petitions<br />\nof all the daughters of Israel<br />\nbe accepted from before <span class=\"divine-referent\">their Mother in heaven</span>,<br />\nand say <em>amen</em>. (<span class=\"instruction\">community:</span> <em>Amen!</em>)\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"jpa-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span style=\"color: dodgerblue;\"><span class=\"instruction\">אשכנזים</span><br />\nיְהֵא שְׁלָמָא רַבָּא מִן־שְׁמַיָא<br />\nחַיִּים טוֹבִים עָלֵֽינוּ<br />\nוְעַל־כׇּל־יִשְׂרָאֵל<br />\nוְעַל־כׇּל־יוֹשְׁבֵי תֵּבֵל<br />\nוְאִמְרוּ אָמֵן: (<span class=\"instruction\">קהל –</span> אָמֵן׃)</span>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span style=\"color: dodgerblue;\"><span class=\"instruction\">Ashkenazim:</span><br />\nMay great peace come from heaven,<br />\ngood life upon us<br />\nand upon all Israel<br />\nand upon all inhabitants of the world,<br />\nand say <em>amen</em>. (<span class=\"instruction\">community:</span> <em>Amen!</em>)</span>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"jpa-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span style=\"color: red;\"><span class=\"instruction\">ספרדים</span><br />\nיְהֵא שְׁלָמָא רַבָּא מִן־שְׁמַיָא<br />\nחַיִּים וְשָׁבָע<br />\nוִישׁוּעָה וְנֶחָמָה<br />\nוְשֵׁיזָבָא וּרְפוּאָה<br />\nוּגְאֻלָּה<br />\nוּסְלִיחָה וְכַפָּרָה<br />\nוְרֵֽוַח וְהַצָּלָה<br />\nלָֽנוּ<br />\nוּלְכׇל־עַמָּהּ יִשְׂרָאֵל<br />\nוְעַל־כׇּל־יוֹשְׁבֵי תֵּבֵל<br />\nוְאִמְרוּ אָמֵן: (<span class=\"instruction\">קהל –</span> אָמֵן׃)</span>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span style=\"color: red;\"><span class=\"instruction\">Sephardim:</span><br />\nMay great peace come from heaven,<br />\nlife and satiety<br />\nand salvation and consolation<br />\nand refuge and healing<br />\nand redemption<br />\nand forgiveness and atonement<br />\nand relief and rescue<br />\nupon us<br />\nand upon all <span class=\"divine-referent\">Her</span> people Israel<br />\nand upon all inhabitants of the world,<br />\nand say <em>amen</em>. (<span class=\"instruction\">community:</span> <em>Amen!</em>)</span>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"jpa-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nמוֹצְאֵת שָׁלוֹם בְּעֵינָיו<br />\nהִיא <span style=\"color: red;\"><span class=\"instruction\">ספרדים</span> בְּרַחֲמֶֽיהָ</span> תּוֹצִיא שָׁלוֹם<br />\nעָלֵֽינוּ<br />\nוְעַל־כׇּל־יִשְׂרָאֵל<br />\nוְעַל־כׇּל־יוֹשְׁבֵי תֵּבֵל<br />\nוְאִמְרוּ אָמֵן:\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nMay <span class=\"divine-referent\">the Finder of Peace</span> in <span class=\"divine-referent\">Her</span> eyes<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_7');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_7');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_7\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[7]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_7\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> A reference to Song of Songs 8:10, as a replacement for the reference to Job 25:2 in the traditional text&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_7').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_7', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\n<span style=\"color: red;\"><span class=\"instruction\">Sephardim:</span> in Her compassion</span> bring out peace<br />\nupon us<br />\nand upon all Israel<br />\nand upon all inhabitants of the world,<br />\nand say <em>amen</em>. (<span class=\"instruction\">community:</span> <em>Amen!</em>)\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class=\"speaker-mute footnotes_reference_container\"> <div class=\"footnote_container_prepare\"><p><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_label pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_expand_collapse_reference_container__1();\">Notes</span><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_collapse_button\" style=\"display: none;; display: none;\" onclick=\"footnote_expand_collapse_reference_container__1();\"></span></p></div> <div id=\"footnote_references_container__1\" style=\"\"><table class=\"footnotes_table footnote-reference-container\"><caption class=\"accessibility\">Notes</caption> <tbody> \r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >1</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">בעשרת ימי תשובה לְעֵֽלָּא לְעֵֽלָּא מִכׇּל־בִּרְכָן</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >2</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">During the ten days of repentance: “high, high above”</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_3\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_3');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >3</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">בארץ ישראל יש מוסיפין: קַדִּישָׁא</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_4\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_4');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >4</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">A neologism, an Aramaic feminine form for “rabbis”</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_5\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_5');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >5</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">An Aramaic feminine form, as opposed to the masculine form used in the traditional text</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_6\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_6');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >6</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">In Israel, some add “holy”</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_7\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_7');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >7</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">A reference to Song of Songs 8:10, as a replacement for the reference to Job 25:2 in the traditional text</td></tr>\r\n\r\n </tbody> </table> </div></div><script type=\"text/javascript\"> function footnote_expand_reference_container__1() { jQuery('#footnote_references_container__1').show(); jQuery('#footnote_reference_container_collapse_button__1').text('−'); } function footnote_collapse_reference_container__1() { jQuery('#footnote_references_container__1').hide(); jQuery('#footnote_reference_container_collapse_button__1').text('+'); } function footnote_expand_collapse_reference_container__1() { if (jQuery('#footnote_references_container__1').is(':hidden')) { footnote_expand_reference_container__1(); } else { footnote_collapse_reference_container__1(); } } function footnote_moveToReference__1(p_str_TargetID) { footnote_expand_reference_container__1(); var l_obj_Target = jQuery('#' + p_str_TargetID); if (l_obj_Target.length) { jQuery( 'html, body' ).delay( 0 ); jQuery('html, body').animate({ scrollTop: l_obj_Target.offset().top - window.innerHeight * 0.2 }, 380); } } function footnote_moveToAnchor__1(p_str_TargetID) { footnote_expand_reference_container__1(); var l_obj_Target = jQuery('#' + p_str_TargetID); if (l_obj_Target.length) { jQuery( 'html, body' ).delay( 0 ); jQuery('html, body').animate({ scrollTop: l_obj_Target.offset().top - window.innerHeight * 0.2 }, 380); } }</script>",
